girder_oauth.providers.base.ProviderBase", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "girder_oauth.providers.base.ProviderBase.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "redirectUri", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "clientId", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "clientSecret", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Base class for OAuth2 providers. The purpose of these classes is to\nperform the user information lookup to their respective provider\nservices in order to return a Girder user given an OAuth2 code that was\nsent to us via a callback.\n\n```\nparam clientId\n\nThe client ID for the given OAuth2 provider.\n\ntype clientId\n\nstr\n\nparam clientSecret\n\nThe client secret for the given OAuth2 provider.\n\ntype clientSecret\n\nstr\n\nparam redirectUri\n\nThe redirect URI used in this OAuth2 flow.\n\ntype redirectUri\n\nstr\n```\n"]}, {"name": "girder_oauth.providers.base.ProviderBase.getProviderName", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "external", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "girder_oauth.providers.base.ProviderBase.getClientIdSetting", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "girder_oauth.providers.base.ProviderBase.getClientSecretSetting", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "girder_oauth.providers.base.ProviderBase.getUrl", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "state", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return the URL to start the OAuth2 authentication flow with an external\nprovider.\n\nThis abstract function must be reimplemented by each provider.\n\n```\nparam state\n\nA unique string, used to prevent CSRF and store other\n```\n\nstate information. This string should not be URL-encoded (that must be\ndone in this method).\n\\:return: An external absolute URL to the start point for this provider's\nOAuth2 flow.\n"]}, {"name": "girder_oauth.providers.base.ProviderBase.getToken", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "code", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "girder_oauth.providers.base.ProviderBase.getUser", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "token", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns a user via this OAuth2 provider, given an OAuth2 access token.\n\nSubclasses must implement this to retrieve a provider-specific unique\nidentifier, email address, first name, last name, and optionally a\nlogin name from the OAuth2 provider, and then call\nself.\\_createOrReuseUser with that information to lookup or create a\ncorresponding Girder user.\n\n```\nparam token\n\nThe current OAuth2 access token.\n\nreturns\n\nThe user document corresponding to this user.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "girder_oauth.providers.base.ProviderBase.addScopes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "scopes", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Plugins wishing to use additional provider features that require other auth\nscopes should use this method to add additional required scopes to the list.\n\n```\nparam scopes\n\nList of additional required scopes.\n\ntype scopes\n\nlist\n\nreturns\n\nThe new list of auth scopes.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "girder_oauth.providers.base.ProviderBase._getJson", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Make an HTTP request using the specified kwargs, then parse it as JSON\nand return the value. If an error occurs, this raises an appropriate\nexception containing the information."]}, {"name": "girder_oauth.providers.base.ProviderBase._createOrReuseUser", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "oauthId", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "email", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "firstName", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lastName", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "userName", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "girder_oauth.providers.base.ProviderBase._generateLogins", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "email", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "firstName", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lastName", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "userName", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Generate a series of reasonable login names for a new user based on\ntheir basic information sent to us by the provider."]}, {"name": "girder_oauth.providers.base.ProviderBase._deriveLogin", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "email", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "firstName", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lastName", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "userName", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Attempt to automatically create a login name from existing user\ninformation from OAuth2 providers. Attempts to generate it from the\nusername on the provider, the email address, or first and last name. If\nnot possible, returns None and it is left to the caller to generate\ntheir own login for the user or choose to fail.\n\n```\nparam email\n\nThe email address.\n\ntype email\n\nstr\n```\n"]}, {"name": "girder_oauth.providers.base.ProviderBase._testLogin", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "